Malema charged with money laundering
Axed ANC Youth League leader Julius Malema arrives for his court appearance in Polokwane on September 26. He was charged with money laundering in a high-profile corruption case his supporters say is part of a political plot to silence President Jacob Zumas most vocal critic. Picture: Reuters
Limpopo - Expelled ANC Youth League president Julius Malema has been charged with money laundering in the Polokwane Regional Court on Wednesday.
"The accused is appearing before the honourable court on charges of money laundering, of receiving the proceeds of unlawful activities," prosecutor Billy Moalusi toldÂ the court.
Prosecutors did not file any other charges. - Reuters, AFP